post_text:
The only thing better than presenting 1 check is presenting 2 checks!
Here are 2 recent recipients of the Eagles Grant: Jess Ellis & John McMillan. These awards will be used to purchase a 3D printer & Ozbots for our students. Our faculty continually go out of their way to enhance our schools!

If you want to help us raise money for awards such as these, please mark your calendar to attend our 2nd annual music fest! It will be held at Conneaut Cellars Winery on Saturday, July 11th. Backwoods Bluegrass will play from 12-2 & Touch of Grey from 2-4. See you there!

post_text:
It is that time of year again..

*Are you a CASH graduating senior with a minimum weighted GPA of 3.0 looking for a scholarship opportunity?*

The Conneaut Eagles Foundation awards a limited number of scholarships to graduating seniors who demonstrate a strong work ethic, proven academic achievement, and plan to study at an accredited college or trade school. For more information or to request an application, check with your Guidance Counselor or send us an email @ Conneaut.Eagles.Foundation@gmail.com! Applications are due via electronic submission by April 15th, 2020 so don't delay!

We look forward to hearing from you!

Please help us spread the word by sharing this post!

post_text:
We would like to thank everyone who helped make our first music event a success! Conneaut Cellars was a beautiful venue where families were able to enjoy soccer & volleyball while listening to some great music from two wonderful local bands! A Touch of Grey & Backwoods Bluegrass entertained for 4 hours; we truly appreciate that our community members were generous enough to donate their time & talent to such a worthy cause! A special thanks to Marquette Bank as well for sponsoring this event! We enjoyed spending the day with those who came out & look forward to seeing more of you next year as we plan to make this an annual event!

With the money raised, we are able to provide one more student scholarship or faculty grant to help our students & teachers!

post_text:
Please join The Conneaut Eagles Foundation for an afternoon of great music, great friends & a great cause! Help The Eagles Foundation provide scholarships to deserving graduating CASH Seniors & grants for important faculty/student projects. Two local bands will play: Touch of Grey, a classic rock cover band, 12-2PM and Backwoods Bluegrass (with past CSD superintendent Rick Rossi) from 2-4PM.

Date: Saturday, October 5th
Time: Noon-4:00 PM
Where: Conneaut Cellars Winery Outside Pavilion & Lawn
Cost: $15/person

Please bring your own lawn chair or blanket & food. Water will be provided & adult beverages can be purchased from the Winery. This event will be held rain or shine under a tent. We suggest car pooling as parking may be limited.

You may purchase tickets at various locals businesses or contact Lora Zill @ timesing@zoominternet.net or send a check made out to the Eagles Foundation to Lora at POB 5276 Conneaut Lake, PA 16316 and she will mail your tix. or drop us a message on Facebook @ Conneaut Eagles Foundation.

Sponsored by Marquette Savings Bank

post_text:
***Faculty, faculty teams, and approved school groups from any of the Conneaut Area School District schools, now is your chance to apply for a grant to create and execute your own supplemental education project***

For a full grant application, send us a FB message, connect with your building principal, or email us at Conneaut.Eagles.Foundation@gmail.com. The deadline to apply is March 30, 2018. Applications must be submitted electronically.

Please note the change in deadline. In order to better accommodate the number of both student scholarship applications & faculty grant application we receive in the spring, we have moved up the faculty grant deadline; we hope you can understand. The fall grant deadline will remain November 15th.

We look forward to reading your application!

post_text: Congratulations to our first Eagles Foundation of Conneaut (PA) School District Scholarship winners: Paige Ransom, Casey York, Sarah Bahner, and Angela Vickers. Each received a $500 scholarship based on an application that demonstrated a strong work ethic, proven academic achievement, and plans to study at an accredited college or trade school. Be sure to let all of your rising seniors know about this opportunity so they can apply next year.
